trong> "}],"hintsAndTricks":["Pasta that is cooked <em>al dente<\/em> is tender but still firm to the bite.","If you prefer not to break the spaghetti in half, you can keep it half and insert it in the top of the mixing bowl, leaving the measuring cup off so it can stick out of the hole. As it begins to cook it will soon disappear into the hole! Replace the measuring cup when the spaghetti has fed through, to preserve the heat."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","35m","6 portions"]}